Nina Westervelt
By T Magazine
Last night, Raf Simons debuted his fall/winter 2018 men’s wear collection, filled with models in heavy outerwear — almost 24 hours after Tom Ford’s offering, in which they wore next to nothing. To see highlights from the New York men’s shows, which mark the culmination of the men’s collections that have spanned London, Florence, Milan and Paris, click through the slide show below (and be sure to check back throughout the week for our coverage of the women’s shows).
